	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Stop and think for a second, please.<BR>
<BR>
If we re-read the original post, we can see why this area does NOT give all binders an advantage over all non-binders, and why this is NOT a &quot;free teleport anywhere&quot; for all binding classes.<BR>
<BR>
1.  The pots are in a very big zone, and far from anything that is accessible.  That means that the first time you go here, you'll have to trek very far out of your way, and most people who are impatient won't want to do that.<BR>
<BR>
2.  The pots do NOT go everywhere; they only go to a dozen locations in Norrath.  Since we can only bind in one location, when we are fighting in LGuk we will have to make a choice:  bind in the Pot Room or bind in UGuk.  If you bind in the pot room and you die, good races will be running from Freeport....<BR>
<BR>
3.  Wizard/druid teleport zones are often more convenient than the firepot destinations.  I, for one, would MUCH rather get a teleport to Feerrott than a teleport to Grobb, just because I'm of a good race, meaning I'm KOS in evil cities.  The Feerrott teleport site is two zones away from LGuk; the closest firepot goes to Freeport, which is at LEAST five zones away (depending on where in Freeport it goes).  Same for reaching SolB -- Lavastorm teleporter or Freeport?  Neriak isn't an option for me.<BR>
<BR>
4.  The pots ARE LOCKED.  No casters get a lockpicking skill, therefore, binding in here will NOT be a free teleport aywhere in the world; it will just be the ability to teleport yourself to the middle of nowhere, at the bottom of an ocean.<BR>
<BR>
5.  The pots ARE LOCKED!  When I die, I go to my bind point buck naked.  No matter who I am, I won't have a lockpick of any kind.  Do you really want to run the risk of accidentally dying and finding yourself an hour and a half away from a bank, naked, at the bottom of an ocean?  This will be the case for every good race in the game.<BR>
<BR>
OK, maybe these pots will save rogues a little bit of time if they are running from Kunark to Permafrost; but they would STILL be far better off getting a TP from a wizard.  This room, and these pots, are a novelty -- nothing more.  Now, if people find a way to open the firepots in the cities, this will hold MUCH more promise, but again -- only for rogues or people with keys.  If I were Verant, I'd make these locks unpickable (or ridiculously hard to pick) and I'd put lore, nodrop keys to ONE box on each dragon/god, as a rare drop.<BR>
<BR>
These things don't unbalance the game because nobody can use them yet.  Depending on the status and rarity of the keys, and whether the firepots are two-way or one-way, I could IMAGINE these changing the game a bit, but they are NOT going to unbalance the game, and they are NOT going to replace druids or wizards.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
									
